@Polymarket Enterprises don't just pick the best model.

They pick the one they trust with sensitive data, compliance requirements, and production systems.

Anthropic quietly won that trust while OpenAI was chasing consumer headlines.

@itsthewealth4me Demand is greater than supply. 

The drama with Anthropic secondary stock is proof we don't have enough companies for investors to invest in. 

Add in Berkshire having $300 billion in cash and who knows how many others sitting on the sidelines waiting for deals.
